{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/tiredness-fatigue-in-adults/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"5b2c98da-05b4-5b25-badd-33cffca97860","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 15054355-4bce-4f94-a504-a7f2018984cb --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 15054355-4bce-4f94-a504-a7f2018984cb -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 6b2add46-8559-4763-9cb5-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field e8c57a46-86e5-4129-8ead-a7f2018984cb --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field e8c57a46-86e5-4129-8ead-a7f2018984cb --><!-- begin field 8f51446b-beb0-4154-8241-a7f2018984cb --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field 8f51446b-beb0-4154-8241-a7f2018984cb --><!-- begin field 0d34c8d9-e53f-42a1-a6eb-a7f2018984cb --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field 0d34c8d9-e53f-42a1-a6eb-a7f2018984cb --><!-- begin field 76ec4254-921b-4314-ba15-a7f2018984cb --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field 76ec4254-921b-4314-ba15-a7f2018984cb --><!-- begin field be5c4fba-cabd-40c3-b16e-a7f2018984cb --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field be5c4fba-cabd-40c3-b16e-a7f2018984cb --><!-- begin field 78eb9236-e860-49b8-8cc0-a7f2018984cb --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field 78eb9236-e860-49b8-8cc0-a7f2018984cb --><!-- end item 6b2add46-8559-4763-9cb5-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"61f35df8-36d2-541e-b997-0b78bad96289","topicId":"21fb5f0f-1e06-43c8-990f-bcded8cfc676","topicName":"Tiredness/fatigue in adults","slug":"tiredness-fatigue-in-adults","lastRevised":"Last revised in March 2020","chapters":[{"id":"404cb5e0-c0b1-516d-b548-9486e82f51b3","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"defb4b1a-b1c0-5607-98c7-67099c37b768","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"630ed210-1441-537d-a2e4-80c614c19753","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"4af39332-0dc0-5737-9443-75ab1ccb7e46","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"499e2dc9-675d-5c9c-8e90-33be13310544","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"6d9550cf-4496-5399-9386-2221acab329e","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"124b7023-365f-54a7-a251-a963db2de643","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"fdfc586d-81b1-5d44-a036-a438634061a5","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"56625d11-efe9-5e3f-b417-bc52a5fd8647","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"709f0c15-0a45-522f-ad1f-264575775c32","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"bbcffc23-5ef8-55a0-a824-0e0d22076edb","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"7fe1e226-6357-5456-a7f9-c486054d1473","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"be53ee8c-6122-5698-a5a7-1faf3f498cff","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"da4f6bbb-2c1d-53cd-975d-e679b502e8c9","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"add551e4-2d3b-5eca-b185-62b80e4e7446","slug":"causes","fullItemName":"Causes"},{"id":"127b3983-553b-546e-8f62-ab5da77e7988","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"46e6e501-33ea-5972-a2db-78fa9832e8bb","slug":"risk-factors","fullItemName":"Risk factors"},{"id":"c3ac446e-5c06-55ac-85b8-487c1c11574c","slug":"complications","fullItemName":"Complications"},{"id":"158c640f-faae-5124-bb17-fc5f80bbcd02","slug":"prognosis","fullItemName":"Prognosis"}]},{"id":"2793dae3-1f43-5720-8d6a-024765f1a4fb","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagnosis","subChapters":[{"id":"60b0af18-e161-532f-80e9-d126e6b8fdfe","slug":"assessment","fullItemName":"Assessment"},{"id":"adeaf5f9-6f69-5d16-a417-6c3e96ba3b0d","slug":"diagnosis-of-cfs","fullItemName":"Diagnosis of CFS"},{"id":"118b8d1b-eabf-5783-b6d9-bf741008d8c3","slug":"investigations","fullItemName":"Investigations"}]},{"id":"d20f8dd6-6b85-52a1-b3f0-991e89e6578d","fullItemName":"Management","slug":"management","subChapters":[{"id":"d03a188b-cced-5325-b1c4-2a0b5f3d6156","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Scenario: Management"}]},{"id":"fb121999-e011-54b3-ba46-e7254fe5cec3","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"c497ff8c-06b6-56cf-aec2-5b3475c6443d","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","sub